where , and since we have
insisted that  is even, the power  must be negative.  It
is then easy to see that the surface  corresponds to 
and it cannot be reached by a physical observer in a finite proper
time.  Thus the two regions are worlds apart  for their
internal observers. The "mirror" and the "real" world do not mix
up!(The idea of
  mirror worlds was introduced many years ago by Yu. Kozarev, L. Okun
  and E.  Pomeranchuck. Glashow has
  shown that the particles of the two worlds cannot interact. It is
  interesting that we come to a similar conclusion and from a
  completely different direction.) 

